<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title><%= pkg.name %></title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="<%= css %>" media="all" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>HTML5 History API is <span id="status"></span></p>

    <p>Instructions:</p>

    <p>When clicking on the navigation links, prevent normal navigation.
      Instead, push a new state object onto the history stack. The state
      object should have the title (from the link text) and url (from the
      link href).</p>
    <p>Clicking on the Current State button should show the current state
      object (serialized json is fine).</p>
    <p>When the history is changed (either via browser back button,
       `history.back()` or `history.forward()`, append a new list item
       showing the state object's title to the history list below (`ol#history`)</p>

    <nav id="nav">
      <ul>
        <li><a href="home">home</a></li>
        <li><a href="music">music</a></li>
        <li><a href="video">video</a></li>
        <li><a href="contact">contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <button id="show-state">Current State</button>
    <p id="current-state"></p>

    <p>History</p>
    <ol id="history"> </ol>

    <script type="text/javascript" src="<%= js %>"></script>
  </body>
</html>
